1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:03,375
When they first brought us in through the door, there was a prefab room

2
00:00:03,750 --> 00:00:05,166
He leaves you standing in the prefab room

3
00:00:05,791 --> 00:00:10,166
He takes whatever personal items you have, he takes your belongings

4
00:00:10,666 --> 00:00:13,208
After you are handed to him by a <i>Hisba</i> member

5
00:00:14,083 --> 00:00:16,958
The <i>Hisba</i> member who brought you in the car hands you over to the man in the room

6
00:00:17,375 --> 00:00:20,583
Then other men come, take you, and escort you to the holding area

7
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:24,208
Inside the prefab room he blindfolded me

8
00:00:25,375 --> 00:00:27,208
And he took me some distance

9
00:00:27,791 --> 00:00:30,250
But I knew I was still inside the church

10
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:32,458
But where inside it he took me, I don’t know

11
00:00:33,041 --> 00:00:36,500
About 15 to 20 meters on foot

12
00:00:36,791 --> 00:00:38,458
And we went up the stairs and entered the room

13
00:00:38,750 --> 00:00:39,791
And when we entered

14
00:00:40,208 --> 00:00:43,750
The total number there was about seven, eight, or nine, around that

15
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,333
When you go in, you’re terrified, you don’t know what your fate will be

16
00:00:48,666 --> 00:00:51,958
You might be released or kept, die, be executed, or be killed, you don’t know

17
00:00:52,750 --> 00:00:55,875
I saw elderly prisoners

18
00:00:56,208 --> 00:00:57,541
And there were young ones too

19
00:00:57,750 --> 00:00:59,125
And some were brought in for smoking

20
00:00:59,500 --> 00:01:01,166
Or because of their pants

21
00:01:01,750 --> 00:01:03,250
Or for not keeping up with prayer

22
00:01:04,208 --> 00:01:06,625
Or for walking in the street, and so on

23
00:01:06,791 --> 00:01:08,041
For many other things

24
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:11,541
They kept bringing two or three in and taking others out, nonstop like that

25
00:01:12,125 --> 00:01:15,083
There were two who stayed, I was taken out, and they remained there

26
00:01:15,625 --> 00:01:16,708
Interviewer: What were their charges?

27
00:01:16,791 --> 00:01:22,083
Their charges—I don’t know, they had problems and there was a case against them

28
00:01:23,083 --> 00:01:24,375
Related to women or something like that

29
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:27,416
As I remember, because their case was very serious

30
00:01:27,833 --> 00:01:29,875
According to what I heard from someone

31
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,416
Interviewer: Do you mean their case was about women?
Witness: Yes, because of women

32
00:01:33,541 --> 00:01:36,416
Interviewer: So the case was among themselves? No one had filed a complaint against them?

33
00:01:36,541 --> 00:01:40,125
No, no, I mean they were caught in the act with women

34
00:01:40,250 --> 00:01:41,250
Interviewer: Do you mean an adultery case?

35
00:01:41,375 --> 00:01:44,458
Yes, an adultery case, and those two were with one woman

36
00:01:44,541 --> 00:01:46,500
And for that reason they were kept here

37
00:01:46,833 --> 00:01:51,333
Interviewer: The woman who was with them, did they tell you which court they took her to?

38
00:01:51,416 --> 00:01:53,958
No, no, they took the woman

39
00:01:54,333 --> 00:01:55,541
But they put her in a different place

40
00:01:55,875 --> 00:01:58,041
Interviewer: Was there a women’s prison in this place?

41
00:01:58,500 --> 00:01:59,916
You can expect anything from them

42
00:02:00,083 --> 00:02:03,416
Because there are many rooms, this one and others

43
00:02:03,583 --> 00:02:05,500
And on the other side, that was also a prison

44
00:02:06,833 --> 00:02:08,750
Interviewer: So you didn’t hear women’s voices?

45
00:02:09,083 --> 00:02:13,291
No, I didn’t, but there were sounds of torture

46
00:02:13,416 --> 00:02:15,500
Mostly at night and at dawn, especially at night

47
00:02:16,916 --> 00:02:20,166
Interviewer: How many days did you stay in this room, which is a cell?

48
00:02:20,375 --> 00:02:22,083
About eight days or nine days

49
00:02:22,375 --> 00:02:23,875
Interviewer: Eight days or nine days

50
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:28,791
When you entered the room, did they take you straight to the judge for interrogation?

51
00:02:28,958 --> 00:02:31,250
Or did you stay for a while, and then they took you to the Investigative Judge?

52
00:02:31,500 --> 00:02:34,000
No, I stayed until the second day, then they referred me to the judge
